Section 1:
1 L.D. 277
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
4 STATE OF MAINE
5 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
6 132ND LEGISLATURE
7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 HOUSE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 181,
9 L.D. 277, “An Act to Repeal the Law Prohibiting Places of Business from Being Open to
10 the Public on Sunday”
11 Amend the amendment in section 2 in paragraph HH (page 1, line 27 in amendment)
12 by inserting after the following: "Day" the following: 'only between the hours of 7 a.m. and
13 noon'
14 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
15 section number to read consecutively.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This amendment restricts the time a grocery store that has no more than 10,000 square
1188 feet of interior customer selling space may be open on Thanksgiving Day to between 7 a.m.
1199 and noon.
2200 SPONSORED BY: ___________________________________
2211 (Speaker FECTEAU, R.)
2222 TOWN: Biddeford
